    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just a metaphor though. it's literal. i look in the mirror and i don't see a person, i just see a biological machine that keeps moving because it has to. there is no spark. no soul. if the art is gone, then the thing that was supposed to inhabit this body is gone. what's the point of maintaining the vessel if there's nobody home anymore?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
